        </gramGrp>
        <def>① Illness Sign of qi rushing upward from the abdomen, contrary to its normal direction, and leaving the body as hiccough with a very brief sound. Wei sheng bao jian 衛生寶鑒 12: 氣短促， 呃逆不絕，不得安臥 , “The qi [leaving] is very brief and urgent. [One experiences] hiccough with a counterflow [of qi] that does not end. One is unable to find rest and sleep”.</def>
      </sense>
      <sense>
        <gramGrp>
          <pos>N</pos>
          <tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-a8e89bab-49e1-4426-b230-0ec7887fd8b4">NP</tls:syn-func>
        </gramGrp>
        <def>② Pathological Condition manifesting itself mainly as hiccough. Wei sheng bao jian 衛生寶鑒 12: 羌活附子湯，治呃逆 , “Decoction with jiang huo and fu zi cures hiccough with counterflow [of qi] ”.</def>
      </sense>
